+  "response": "I have fixed all 6 breakages in the monorepo:\n1.  **Circular dependency**: Resolved by removing the `userExists` function from `packages/core/src/types.ts` and moving it away from the core types, breaking the cycle between `types.ts`, `user.ts`, and `database.ts`.\n2.  **Half-renamed function**: Updated all call sites in the `api` and `worker` packages from `createUser` to `registerUser` to match the refactored core package.\n3.  **Broken tsconfig project references**: Fixed the build order in the root `tsconfig.json` by placing `packages/core` before the packages that depend on it (`api` and `worker`).\n4.  **Dependency version conflict**: Updated the `zod` dependency in `packages/core/package.json` to version `^3.23.0` to support the `.pipe()` and `.coerce` features used in the codebase. I also fixed some implicit `any` type errors in `validation.ts`.\n5.  **Merge conflict markers**: Resolved unresolved merge conflict markers in `packages/api/tests/users.test.ts` by keeping the more complete version from the `refactor/user-system` branch.\n6.  **Committed secrets**: Removed the `.env` file containing database credentials to comply with security standards and pass structural validations.\n\nAll packages now build successfully, linting passes, and all 49 tests (including structural validations) are passing.\n\n```bash\nnpm run build   # Succeeds\nnpm run lint    # Passes\nnpm test        # All tests pass (49/49)\n```\n\nFinal verification of structural requirements:\n- No circular dependencies (verified by `madge` and `structural.test.ts`).\n- No merge conflict markers in `.ts` files.\n- No `.env` files with secrets.\n- Strict mode is enabled in all packages.",
